{
  "meta": {
    "id": "playback-live",
    "description": "Live playback happy-path for the real-hls.js smoke. Flow (verified against usePlaybackOrchestrator.ts / useLiveSessionController.ts / generated client types.gen.ts as of 2026-05-24): POST /live/stream-info returns the playback contract (mode=hlsjs + playbackDecisionToken; live decisions carry no outputUrl — the HLS URL comes from the session) -> POST /intents returns 202 IntentAcceptedResponse {sessionId, requestId, status:accepted} -> GET /sessions/{id} polled until state=READY with playbackUrl + heartbeatIntervalSeconds -> POST /sessions/{id}/heartbeat. The decision token is MANDATORY for live (orchestrator fails closed without it); the contracts.playbackInfoDecision capability does NOT gate it (useCapabilities is a hardcoded stub). Session id is fixed to 'e2e-live-1' so the dynamic /sessions/{id} endpoints match the exact-path fixture server. HLS playlist + segments are served by the fixture-server static route under /api/v3/sessions/{id}/hls/, not by these endpoints. Known matcher limitation: stream.start and stream.stop are both POST /intents and cannot be distinguished by path."
  },
  "capabilities": {
    "contracts.playbackInfoDecision": "absent"
  },
  "endpoints": [
    {
      "method": "GET",
      "path": "/api/v3/system/capabilities",
      "response": { "status": 200, "body": { "contracts.playbackInfoDecision": "absent" } }
